When I group with friends, /ran 100 is fine if there is ever an item we need to roll on, as it rarely comes up since NBG wins out in those groups.  But occassionally something comes up that either everyone could use or nobody needs.<br>
<br>
When I do the occassional pick up group, /ran 100 is also usually fine.  But I do prefer to /ran for the seed if I'm in with complete strangers on a long camp/big item.  Just to be safe.  Even with this system you're going to get someone to complain.  Whoever loses the roll is never happy.  I had this recently in fact, was in a group with a common spawn but rare drop, finally got the drop we all were looking for, and they ask &quot;/ran 100?&quot;  and I suggest a random for seed  (( I was camping the spawn alone, but agreed to share when they came - I found it only fair that I could suggest the random)).  So I roll, and get the seed - somewhere around 500.. then we all roll, and luckily I win.  Yay me!<br>
